        <section id="Definition" class="tabcontent" style="display:block;">
            <h2>Definition</h2>
            <p>
                Saving water means using water wisely and avoiding unnecessary waste. By adopting simple habits and efficient technologies, we can reduce our water use at home, school, and in our communities.
            </p>
            <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1502741338009-cac2772e18bc?auto=format&fit=crop&w=800&q=80" alt="Glass of water symbolizing conservation" class="topic-img">
        </section>

        <section id="Causes" class="tabcontent">
            <h2>Causes</h2>
            <p>
                Main challenges leading to water wastage include:
            </p>
            <ul>
                <li>Leaking taps, pipes, or toilets wasting water unnoticed.</li>
                <li>Overusing water for everyday activities.</li>
                <li>Pollution making water unsafe to reuse.</li>
                <li>Climate changes causing droughts and supply shortages.</li>
            </ul>
            <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1464983953574-0892a716854b?auto=format&fit=crop&w=800&q=80" alt="Water wastage and pollution" class="topic-img">
        </section>

        <section id="Effect" class="tabcontent">
            <h2>Effect</h2>
            <p>
                When water isn't saved:
            </p>
            <ul>
                <li>Droughts can cause water shortages and restrictions.</li>
                <li>People may need to travel far to collect water.</li>
                <li>Plants, animals, and the entire environment suffer.</li>
                <li>Lack of water can make it harder to keep places clean and healthy.</li>
            </ul>
            <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1506784983877-45594efa4cbe?auto=format&fit=crop&w=800&q=80" alt="People affected by water scarcity" class="topic-img">
        </section>

        <section id="Solutions" class="tabcontent">
            <h2>Solutions</h2>
            <p>
                Ways to help save water every day:
            </p>
            <ul>
                <li>Fix leaks and turn off taps when not in use.</li>
                <li>Take shorter showers and reuse water when possible.</li>
                <li>Use water-saving devices at home and school.</li>
                <li>Spread awareness on water conservation in your community!</li>
            </ul>
            <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1528825871115-3581a5387919?auto=format&fit=crop&w=800&q=80" alt="Child washing hands at a water-saving tap" class="topic-img">
        </section>

